WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.967
A source adapter pins an immutable revision and extracts candidate logic with exact provenance.

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.967
Each candidate becomes Canonical Rule IR: explicit inputs, conditions, outcomes, and source locations.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:18.600
A maker creates a new revision. An independent checker compares it with the source evidence.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:25.700
Golden cases execute that pinned revision, comparing actual decisions with governed expected outputs.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:32.967
Passing evidence opens the release gate. Revisions, approvals, test runs, and artifacts remain traceable.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:40.900
Mode A publishes approved IR to the managed runtime. Mode B generates deterministic source and a reviewable code change.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.033
One governed model, traced from source to production.
